1199
01:22:39,245 --> 01:22:41,907
Motion by Councilor Lococo to revert back to regular business.

1200
01:22:44,835 --> 01:23:04,078
16-0-6, 17-0-6-3, offered by Councilor Falco, whereas the Medford Board of Appeals meets on a monthly basis to make decisions about various projects and developments, whereas many of the meetings are conducted in room 201 in Medford City Hall, where there is a limited amount of seating.

1201
01:23:05,599 --> 01:23:13,720
Be it resolved that moving forward that all Medford Board of Appeals meetings take place in all the chambers at City Hall to give all residents

1202
01:23:14,558 --> 01:23:17,160
the opportunity to attend and to participate.

1203
01:23:17,300 --> 01:23:18,260
Counselor Belko.

1204
01:23:19,341 --> 01:23:20,542
Thank you, Mr. President.

1205
01:23:21,302 --> 01:23:35,211
Throughout the years, I've gone to many Board of Appeals meetings just to see different, just to, you know, when the different issues come up on the agenda, just go down and take a look to see what's going on in the community.

1206
01:23:35,791 --> 01:23:39,353
And I mean, I've gotten calls from other people as well that have attended these meetings.

1207
01:23:39,954 --> 01:23:41,715
And usually the meetings are held in room 201,

1208
01:23:43,537 --> 01:23:47,298
for the most part, and in room 201, there's very limited seating.

1209
01:23:47,939 --> 01:23:57,862
I think it's about maybe 20 seats, a table up in the front, and it seems like any meeting you go to, if there's a big issue, there are a number of people just standing in the hallways.

1210
01:23:57,902 --> 01:24:11,846
They can't weigh in on any type of issue, or they have to wait in line, or they missed a presentation that maybe the developer's giving, and it just doesn't seem, in this day and age, like it's a proper place to have a meeting.

1211
01:24:12,524 --> 01:24:13,985
There's no audio visual equipment.

1212
01:24:14,445 --> 01:24:16,407
There's, it's just too small.

1213
01:24:17,027 --> 01:24:18,428
I don't find it very transparent.

1214
01:24:18,448 --> 01:24:23,011
If you have to wait in the hallway and you can't even hear what's going on in the room, it doesn't make sense.

1215
01:24:23,432 --> 01:24:24,352
We live in a big city.

1216
01:24:24,853 --> 01:24:28,455
We've over 55,000 close to 60,000 people live here.

1217
01:24:29,616 --> 01:24:31,377
This community is hot for development.

1218
01:24:31,877 --> 01:24:39,903
People want to develop and there are many development meetings and zoning board decisions that have happened in the past and that will be happening in the future.

1219
01:24:40,787 --> 01:24:46,771
and everyone should be able to weigh in on these different issues that come before the zoning board.

1220
01:24:48,573 --> 01:24:50,574
If I may finish.

1221
01:24:52,155 --> 01:24:56,859
In my opinion, I believe that those meetings should be held here in chambers.

1222
01:24:57,119 --> 01:25:03,063
I know they meet on Tuesday night usually, which is the same night as us, but what they can do is maybe they can move to Wednesday nights.

1223
01:25:03,743 --> 01:25:05,024
They can pick a different night.

1224
01:25:05,205 --> 01:25:09,788
Wednesday nights, I don't think this chamber is being used on a regular basis, but it needs to be looked at.

1225
01:25:10,653 --> 01:25:24,525
We need to make this process—we need to bring the process into the 21st century where people can come, if there's a presentation, they can use the AV equipment here, but it shouldn't be in a room where you could barely fit 20 people and people feel like they're excluded.

1226
01:25:25,626 --> 01:25:27,608
You know, government should be transparent.

1227
01:25:27,648 --> 01:25:28,489
That's what it's all about.

1228
01:25:28,989 --> 01:25:31,671
People should have access, and I think this would be a better venue.

1229
01:25:32,132 --> 01:25:32,452
Thank you.

1230
01:25:32,492 --> 01:25:33,273
I think the question is,

1231
01:25:33,797 --> 01:25:35,198
The meeting should be moved to Wednesday night.

1232
01:25:35,218 --> 01:25:39,442
So because the Board of Heals does meet on a Tuesday evening, the same as we do.

1233
01:25:39,682 --> 01:25:40,883
Absolutely.

1234
01:25:42,084 --> 01:25:47,388
If we could amend it to actually have them move their night to Wednesday night and have it here in council chambers.

1235
01:25:47,468 --> 01:25:47,869
Thank you.

1236
01:25:47,889 --> 01:25:49,190
Thank you, Mr. President.

1237
01:25:49,230 --> 01:25:50,451
As amended by Councilor Falco.

1238
01:25:50,531 --> 01:25:51,352
Councilor Longo-Kern.

1239
01:25:51,512 --> 01:25:53,033
Thank you, President Carviello.

1240
01:25:53,193 --> 01:25:56,056
I second the paper, second approval for the motion.

1241
01:25:57,697 --> 01:25:59,278
I've received complaints myself.

1242
01:25:59,358 --> 01:26:00,840
And as we come in on a Tuesday night,

1243
01:26:01,644 --> 01:26:07,448
during the once a month when the Zoning Board of Appeals meets, we see a crowd outside the hallway.

1244
01:26:07,488 --> 01:26:11,831
And I have received complaints about people that weren't able to speak, they weren't able to hear.

1245
01:26:12,251 --> 01:26:17,915
And I think it's extremely important that anybody and everybody be able to hear any meeting that goes on at City Hall.

1246
01:26:18,375 --> 01:26:23,899
But time after time, month after month, that is the one board that meets where the doors are overflowing.

1247
01:26:23,919 --> 01:26:27,782
Because you have attorneys, you have residents, you have business owners.

1248
01:26:28,267 --> 01:26:30,808
People from the city council do want to attend.

1249
01:26:30,868 --> 01:26:31,688
We're not able to.

1250
01:26:32,048 --> 01:26:34,148
So I agree with moving it to another night.

1251
01:26:34,569 --> 01:26:36,689
I also agree that here would be the right place.

1252
01:26:37,209 --> 01:26:41,410
I would ask that we amend this and request that the meetings be televised as well.

1253
01:26:42,110 --> 01:26:47,252
I think we need to start moving more and more towards televised board and commission meetings.

1254
01:26:47,312 --> 01:26:50,692
And that is one of the biggest and most important boards we have in the city.

1255
01:26:51,092 --> 01:26:57,394
And it's something that I would definitely want to attend more often or at least be able to have that opportunity to watch from home.

1256
01:26:58,116 --> 01:27:04,381
We as city councilors are being asked to get involved with certain projects and ask for help.

1257
01:27:04,441 --> 01:27:05,642
Neighbors are asking us for help.

1258
01:27:05,702 --> 01:27:14,929
So it's important that we have that opportunity to not only watch the meetings, attend the meetings, speak at the meetings, but everybody should be able to attend the meetings and be able to hear and speak.

1259
01:27:15,350 --> 01:27:22,495
So I think it's a great resolve, and I think it's definitely a positive, and I move approval, or second the approval of Councilor Falco.

1260
01:27:23,056 --> 01:27:23,856
Thank you, Councilor.

1261
01:27:24,117 --> 01:27:24,617
Councilor Knight.

1262
01:27:25,418 --> 01:27:27,640
